<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-555-152  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 555 152.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  June 11 1990 v7 n23 p4(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Development system produces efficient Cobol code for VMS.andO;(Synthesis computer Technologies Syntek Case/Ap) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Synthesis Computer Technologies Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Syntek Case/Ap (Program development software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCOBOLApplications ProgrammingSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Development system produces efficient Cobol code for VMSandM;LONG BEACH, Calif.andP;  -- Synthesis Computer Technologies will unveil aCobol-based application generation system for VMS at the Dexpo East tradeshow in Boston later this month.andM;Based on a Cobol code generator, Syntek Case/Ap lets users define and createa prototype, then refine it through an iterative process until the finalapplication is completed, company officials said.andM;&quot;It helps improve the productivity of a Cobol programmer by producingprograms that are very efficient and easy to maintain.andP;  You start with asimple application and increase in complexity through an iterative process ofrefinement.andP;  Programs developed [with Case/Ap] are efficient, structured andvery easy to maintain,&quot; said Robert Murialdo, Synthesis' president.andM;Syntek Case/Ap uses modularized coding techniques for fast source-codegeneration and low software-maintenance costs, and the main system requiresonly an additional Cobol compiler to create fully documented, executableapplications, the officials said.andM;Syntek Case/Ap includes Devcon, a development environment controller thatallows access to different modules; Syntek TED, a terminal editor withautomatic documentation generation for data models and applicationspecifications; Syntek GED, a graphical editor that allows access to thesystem from X windows terminals; Syntek Format, a forms editor; and SyntekTEP, a text processor.andM;Also available with Syntek Case/Ap are Syntek QL and Syntex RG, which provideunstructured data queries and interactive report generation, respectively,the officials said.andM;Other features include a library of program routines such as date arithmetic,terminal I/O functions and data file access; an audit trail utility; a datadictionary compiler; a data access routine generator that implements the datamodel; and an access control system that regulates data access at the logicalfile and record levels, the officials said.andM;The product includes Syntek run-time routines and is capable of accessingdata stored in both RMS and Rdb files, company officials said.andM;Syntek Case/Ap versions for Unix and IBM operating systems are underdevelopment.andP;  The VMS version is priced from $5,000 on a VAXstation to$75,000 on high-end VAX systems.andM;For additional information, Synthesis Computer Technologies Inc. can becontacted at 5199 E. Pacific Coast Highway, Suite 601, Long Beach.andP;  CA 90804,(213) 494-4069.andO;</TEXT></DOC>